I can't believe this is the same house.

794
00:45:02.679 --> 00:45:04.782
I know. Isn't it great?

795
00:45:05.099 --> 00:45:06.977
It's their wedding present.

796
00:45:07.468 --> 00:45:09.178
Not everybody feels like my father.

797
00:45:10.258 --> 00:45:12.919
They wanted to do
something special for us.

798
00:45:13.401 --> 00:45:15.070
-Say thank you.
-Thank you.

799
00:45:15.939 --> 00:45:17.710
It's very special.

800
00:45:18.675 --> 00:45:20.012
Don't worry about it.

801
00:45:21.827 --> 00:45:23.053
You don't like it.

802
00:45:24.103 --> 00:45:27.257
No. no. I just never lived
in anything so bright and...

803
00:45:27.408 --> 00:45:28.910
Jesus Christ!

804
00:45:30.685 --> 00:45:31.967
Isn't it beautiful?

805
00:45:32.475 --> 00:45:33.375
It's an antique.

806
00:45:33.436 --> 00:45:36.217
It's been in my family for centuries.
It will protect us.

807
00:45:36.696 --> 00:45:38.934
Couldn't we just trade
Cujo in for a Doberman?

808
00:45:39.164 --> 00:45:40.925
That isn't funny Alex.

809
00:45:41.250 --> 00:45:44.057
You're hurting my baby's feelings.

810
00:45:44.470 --> 00:45:46.655
Hey. what did your parents say
when you told them?

811
00:45:47.377 --> 00:45:48.801
Oh. you know. I feel so stupid.

812
00:45:48.862 --> 00:45:50.802
I forgot they went to
Europe for the summer.

813
00:45:52.631 --> 00:45:53.536
It's April.

814
00:45:53.635 --> 00:45:55.226
They like to get there early.

815
00:45:56.362 --> 00:45:58.955
So you did all this in one day?

816
00:45:59.209 --> 00:46:00.780
I should hire you to build the club.

817
00:46:01.437 --> 00:46:03.947
-Well. I don't know that you can afford us.
-Ah.

818
00:46:06.271 --> 00:46:07.762
You are so cute.

819
00:46:08.432 --> 00:46:09.230
Here.

820
00:46:09.639 --> 00:46:12.874
I'm gonna go get my camera and
take a picture of my family.

821
00:46:19.829 --> 00:46:20.832
What are you lookin' at?

822
00:47:20.879 --> 00:47:23.382
# Siguen los pregones

823
00:47:23.443 --> 00:47:25.673
# La melancolia

824
00:47:25.734 --> 00:47:30.010
# Cada noche junto a la Luna Sigue
El guajiro entonando El son #

825
00:47:30.382 --> 00:47:32.937
# Cada calle que va a mi pueblo #

826
00:47:32.998 --> 00:47:35.996
# Tiene un quejido Tiene un lamento #

827
00:47:36.064 --> 00:47:37.785
# La nostalgia decimos

828
00:47:37.846 --> 00:47:42.133
# Te llega con fuerza al
corazon La tierra Te duele #

829
00:47:42.644 --> 00:47:44.379
# La tierra Te da

830
00:47:45.086 --> 00:47:47.277
# En medio del Alma

831
00:47:47.338 --> 00:47:49.864
# Cuando tu no estas

832
00:47:49.964 --> 00:47:54.250
# La tierra Te empuja Tierra y cigal #

833
00:47:54.723 --> 00:47:57.094
# La tierra suspira

834
00:47:57.155 --> 00:47:59.491
# Si no Te ve mas #

835
00:48:02.423 --> 00:48:03.644
Alex!

836
00:48:06.502 --> 00:48:07.047
Oh.

837
00:48:08.183 --> 00:48:10.468
So this is where you go every day.

838
00:48:11.164 --> 00:48:12.099
It opened last night.

839
00:48:12.168 --> 00:48:14.667
I got a lot of complaints. I think
the fact that that there are no...

840
00:48:15.795 --> 00:48:17.697
walls upset people.

841
00:48:18.446 --> 00:48:21.647
Well. it's going to be
wonderful. I can tell.

842
00:48:22.484 --> 00:48:24.185
I wanted you to be the first guest

843
00:48:25.140 --> 00:48:26.224
at our best table.

844
00:48:29.944 --> 00:48:31.528
I'm very honoured.

845
00:48:36.491 --> 00:48:38.734
Oh. Alex. this is so romantic.

846
00:48:40.888 --> 00:48:42.026
The candles...

847
00:48:42.171 --> 00:48:44.438
and the wine... I mean. the milk.

848
00:48:45.273 --> 00:48:47.039
Mmm. and pizza.

849
00:48:47.834 --> 00:48:48.755
It's perfect.

850
00:48:49.167 --> 00:48:51.309
Nope. perfect would be
if this was New York

851
00:48:51.370 --> 00:48:53.495
and that was a Gray's Papaya hot dog.

852
00:48:53.951 --> 00:48:55.672
What's a Gray Papaya?

853
00:48:55.851 --> 00:48:58.317
Broadway and 72nd.
Four blocks from my apartment.

854
00:48:58.378 --> 00:48:59.413
The best...

855
00:48:59.864 --> 00:49:01.542
hot dog in the world.

856
00:49:01.795 --> 00:49:02.557
Mmm.

857
00:49:03.787 --> 00:49:05.493
And if we were in Mexico.

858
00:49:05.561 --> 00:49:07.061
we would be eating...

859
00:49:08.054 --> 00:49:08.722
Ah!

860
00:49:08.783 --> 00:49:11.053
-Albondigas.
-Albondigas.

861
00:49:12.244 --> 00:49:15.250
They're this sort of meatball soup.

862
00:49:15.470 --> 00:49:17.611
My great grandmother is famous for them.

863
00:49:19.012 --> 00:49:21.152
Oh. Alex. you have
to come with me one day.

864
00:49:21.488 --> 00:49:22.920
You'd love it there.

865
00:49:23.308 --> 00:49:26.487
There are no phones. no
electricity. no people.

866
00:49:27.785 --> 00:49:28.682
No kidding?

867
00:49:31.945 --> 00:49:32.723
You know...

868
00:49:33.119 --> 00:49:35.609
there's a spot in the
middle of Central Park...

869
00:49:35.751 --> 00:49:36.836
the Bethesda Fountain...

870
00:49:36.897 --> 00:49:38.376
If you sit there long enough.

871
00:49:38.928 --> 00:49:40.761
the entire city walks by.

872
00:49:41.223 --> 00:49:42.191
Hmm.

873
00:49:43.914 --> 00:49:46.073
And I know of this one canyon.

874
00:49:46.297 --> 00:49:48.072
that if you sit there long enough.

875
00:49:48.676 --> 00:49:51.018
nobody finds you and you die.

876
00:49:53.428 --> 00:49:54.121
Really?

877
00:49:55.902 --> 00:49:57.620
I could not believe it.

878
00:49:57.687 --> 00:49:59.687
The whole night he kept
changing the subject.

879
00:49:59.748 --> 00:50:01.436
New York this. New York that...

880
00:50:01.497 --> 00:50:04.150
What do you expect?
His life is not your life.

881
00:50:04.552 --> 00:50:05.808
I thought you were on my side.

882
00:50:06.011 --> 00:50:07.954
He has a family to support.

883
00:50:08.284 --> 00:50:10.420
He can do that here.
We can do it together.

884
00:50:10.726 --> 00:50:13.300
Marriage is about finding a middle ground.

885
00:50:13.582 --> 00:50:15.600
You have to learn to pick your battles.

886
00:50:16.703 --> 00:50:18.905
I sure picked one this morning.

887
00:50:20.395 --> 00:50:21.897
What did you do?

888
00:50:22.006 --> 00:50:24.959
Nothing. I just had the guys
drop by to take him shooting.

889
00:50:26.047 --> 00:50:28.543
Alex is alone with your brothers?

890
00:50:29.096 --> 00:50:30.119
And Chuy.

891
00:50:31.274 --> 00:50:32.948
I better light another candle.

892
00:50:41.646 --> 00:50:44.648
Isabel said there's some pretty
interesting canyons up here.

893
00:50:44.839 --> 00:50:46.997
One in particular where people go to die?

894
00:50:48.153 --> 00:50:49.732
That's the other way. right?

895
00:50:50.085 --> 00:50:52.596
What's this about you
taking Isabel to New York?

896
00:50:53.558 --> 00:50:55.138
Oh yeah. that's just an idea.

897
00:50:55.199 --> 00:50:57.210
There's nothing carved
in stone or anything.

898
00:50:57.472 --> 00:50:58.677
She won't go!

899
00:50:59.016 --> 00:51:00.376
I'd bet my life on it.

900
00:51:00.876 --> 00:51:01.920
Aw. shucks. Juan.

901
00:51:01.981 --> 00:51:04.047
Nobody here expects someone
to give up his life.

902
00:51:04.594 --> 00:51:08.305
Do they. Chu... y?

903
00:51:11.066 --> 00:51:14.055
What are you going to be?
Isabel Fuentes? Isabel Whitman?

904
00:51:14.116 --> 00:51:16.356
Or are you gonna do a Hillary
and be Isabel Fuentes-Whitman?

905
00:51:16.693 --> 00:51:18.882
That's Mrs. Alex Whitman to you.

906
00:51:19.039 --> 00:51:19.925
Pardon me.

907
00:51:20.419 --> 00:51:22.146
I'm sorry. Excuse me.

908
00:51:22.619 --> 00:51:23.842
Excuse me a moment.

909
00:51:25.090 --> 00:51:27.788
I didn't mean to eavesdrop.
but I couldn't help but overhear.

910
00:51:27.960 --> 00:51:30.017
-Did you just say Alex Whitman?
-Uh-huh.

911
00:51:30.591 --> 00:51:31.834
From New Canaan. Connecticut?

912
00:51:33.628 --> 00:51:35.196
I think that's where he's from.

913
00:51:35.474 --> 00:51:37.700
Late twenties. about six feet tall.

914
00:51:37.761 --> 00:51:39.919
dark hair. talks a lot with his hands.

915
00:51:40.256 --> 00:51:41.268
That's him.

916
00:51:45.142 --> 00:51:45.979
I'm sorry.

917
00:51:46.173 --> 00:51:47.215
I'm Cathy Stewart.

918
00:51:47.477 --> 00:51:49.229
Our families are very old friends.

919
00:51:49.594 --> 00:51:52.699
You're kidding? Oh. that's fantastic.

920
00:51:52.760 --> 00:51:54.683
I really don't know any of his friends.

921
00:51:54.775 --> 00:51:56.470
so I am so glad to meet you.

922
00:51:56.531 --> 00:51:58.636
I'm Isabel. and this is Lanie.

923
00:51:59.428 --> 00:52:00.120
Hi.

924
00:52:01.532 --> 00:52:02.337
Do you know.

925
00:52:02.749 --> 00:52:05.181
I've missed Alex the last
couple of trips out here.

926
00:52:05.557 --> 00:52:06.832
He's always so busy.

927
00:52:07.562 --> 00:52:08.483
How do you know him?

928
00:52:10.624 --> 00:52:11.736
I'm his wife.

929
00:52:13.026 --> 00:52:14.027
I beg your pardon?

930
00:52:15.501 --> 00:52:16.775
Yeah. Alex and I.

931
00:52:17.057 --> 00:52:17.959
we're married.

932
00:52:19.343 --> 00:52:20.065
And...

933
00:52:20.461 --> 00:52:21.584
they're gonna have a baby.

934
00:52:23.081 --> 00:52:23.964
A baby?

935
00:52:24.598 --> 00:52:25.567
Really?

936
00:52:26.453 --> 00:52:27.207
Oh.

937
00:52:28.374 --> 00:52:29.875
well. congratulations.

938
00:52:30.516 --> 00:52:31.157
Wow!

939
00:52:32.208 --> 00:52:33.694
Isn't this a surprise?

940
00:52:36.671 --> 00:52:38.027
Cuidado. muchachos!

941
00:52:42.777 --> 00:52:44.379
This is some backyard.

942
00:52:45.254 --> 00:52:47.122
I can see why you guys like it up here.

943
00:52:48.172 --> 00:52:49.497
It must have been fun growin' up.

944
00:52:54.299 --> 00:52:54.910
You know.

945
00:52:55.072 --> 00:52:56.251
all these rocks.

946
00:52:57.262 --> 00:52:58.645
the open space.

947
00:52:58.912 --> 00:52:59.773
the view.

948
00:53:00.226 --> 00:53:01.234
the birds...

949
00:53:04.130 --> 00:53:05.323
The snakes.

950
00:53:10.090 --> 00:53:11.289
Cascabeles.

951
00:53:22.204 --> 00:53:23.498
Do not move.

952
00:53:25.094 --> 00:53:25.985
Okay. everybody.

953
00:53:26.482 --> 00:53:27.510
we do this on three.

954
00:53:27.959 --> 00:53:28.640
Ready?

955
00:53:34.293 --> 00:53:35.848
-Wait a minute. Wait a minute.
-One!

956
00:53:35.909 --> 00:53:37.618
-What are we doing on three?
-Two!

957
00:53:37.679 --> 00:53:39.289
-What happens on three?
-Three!

958
00:53:46.009 --> 00:53:47.546
I'm coming!

959
00:53:50.588 --> 00:53:51.445
Lucy.

960
00:53:51.755 --> 00:53:53.804
you got some 'splaining to do.

961
00:53:53.919 --> 00:53:56.341
Oh. my God.

962
00:53:56.431 --> 00:53:57.972
What did you do to him?

963
00:53:58.173 --> 00:53:59.651
He fell into some cactus.

964
00:54:00.302 --> 00:54:02.831
A lot of cactus. We gave him
the tequila for the pain.

965
00:54:03.077 --> 00:54:05.112
I think the desert made
a big impression on him.

966
00:54:05.182 --> 00:54:07.476
-I told you to make it special. idiot.
-Ow.

967
00:54:07.588 --> 00:54:10.182
Not to kill him!
Se me salen de aqui todos!

968
00:54:10.258 --> 00:54:12.234
Get out of here. Get the hell outta here.

969
00:54:12.295 --> 00:54:13.412
You too. Come on.

970
00:54:15.590 --> 00:54:16.717
Baby?

971
00:54:19.096 --> 00:54:20.217
Honey?

972
00:54:22.429 --> 00:54:23.874
Whatever you do.

973
00:54:24.818 --> 00:54:25.972
don't turn over.

974
00:54:26.157 --> 00:54:27.755
I'm gonna go get the tweezers.

975
00:54:47.836 --> 00:54:49.185
I'm confused.

976
00:54:50.653 --> 00:54:52.687
If babies can only see in black and white.

977
00:54:52.748 --> 00:54:53.913
then how come that

978
00:54:54.467 --> 00:54:56.066
Barney guy is purple?

979
00:54:57.034 --> 00:54:59.739
Dinosaurs come later. tontito.

980
00:55:01.108 --> 00:55:02.658
Wait. don't sit there.

981
00:55:03.020 --> 00:55:04.365
I'm doing the floors next.

982
00:55:04.564 --> 00:55:05.866
-Again?
-Mm-hmm.

983
00:55:05.927 --> 00:55:08.369
Oh. wait a minute. I read about this.
This is the...

984
00:55:08.522 --> 00:55:09.996
'nesting period'. isn't it?

985
00:55:10.613 --> 00:55:13.685
It must be because I can't seem
to get this place clean enough.

986
00:55:15.052 --> 00:55:15.887
Come here.

987
00:55:20.006 --> 00:55:21.921
Ah. ah. ah!

988
00:55:21.984 --> 00:55:23.914
Oh. I'm sorry. Poor baby.

989
00:55:23.975 --> 00:55:25.890
Yeah. I think there's one still in there.

990
00:55:25.978 --> 00:55:29.096
Then we'll just have to
take these pants off...

991
00:55:29.205 --> 00:55:31.283
so that I can take a closer look.

992
00:55:31.957 --> 00:55:33.547
Whatever you say. doctor.

993
00:55:34.431 --> 00:55:35.795
Oh. I forgot to tell you.

994
00:55:35.856 --> 00:55:38.223
I ran into an old friend
of yours the other day.

995
00:55:38.284 --> 00:55:39.777
Cathy... something.

996
00:55:40.402 --> 00:55:41.379
Cathy Stewart?

997
00:55:41.713 --> 00:55:43.387
-Uh-huh.
-Really?

998
00:55:43.782 --> 00:55:44.413
When?

999
00:55:44.522 --> 00:55:46.766
Last week. the same day as the cactus.

1000
00:55:47.123 --> 00:55:48.429
I think she's jealous.

1001
00:55:48.815 --> 00:55:51.808
-Oh. really?
-Mm-hmm.

1002
00:55:52.974 --> 00:55:53.855
I'll get it.

1003
00:56:00.349 --> 00:56:01.943
Coming! Ow.

1004
00:56:05.094 --> 00:56:06.365
Surprise!

1005
00:56:06.426 --> 00:56:07.648
Mom. Dad.

1006
00:56:09.465 --> 00:56:11.691
I wanted to call first. This was her idea.

1007
00:56:11.752 --> 00:56:14.081
I spoke to Cathy the other
day. and she said...

1008
00:56:14.263 --> 00:56:17.588
we had to get our little fannys out
here and see what you were up to.

1009
00:56:17.657 --> 00:56:20.503
She practically insisted.
What the hell is that?

1010
00:56:21.226 --> 00:56:23.112
-A squirrel?
-Alex!

1011
00:56:23.413 --> 00:56:25.785
-Who is it?
-I got it. hon...

1012
00:56:28.172 --> 00:56:30.458
Now that is what I call a housekeeper.

1013
00:56:31.611 --> 00:56:32.265
Honey.

1014
00:56:32.464 --> 00:56:33.812
did we come at a bad time?

1015
00:56:34.132 --> 00:56:36.162
No. no. She's just...

1016
00:56:36.223 --> 00:56:38.894
She's cleaning the oven.
and the fumes are...

1017
00:56:40.014 --> 00:56:41.337
Well. you're here.

1018
00:56:41.398 --> 00:56:42.762
You're really here.

1019
00:56:47.458 --> 00:56:48.242
Hi.

1020
00:56:49.145 --> 00:56:49.759
Hello.

1021
00:56:52.486 --> 00:56:54.095
Alex. aren't you going to introduce us?

1022
00:56:54.595 --> 00:56:55.717
Yes. uh.

1023
00:56:55.876 --> 00:56:57.457
yes. this is. uh.

1024
00:56:59.925 --> 00:57:00.610
uh...

1025
00:57:01.428 --> 00:57:04.051
-Isabel.
-Isab... Isabel. right.

1026
00:57:04.297 --> 00:57:04.785
Right.

1027
00:57:06.007 --> 00:57:06.885
Isabel.

1028
00:57:07.293 --> 00:57:08.726
It's very nice to meet you.

1029
00:57:08.869 --> 00:57:11.846
I'm Alex's mother. Mrs. Whitman.
and this is Mr. Whitman.

1030
00:57:12.726 --> 00:57:14.691
Oh. my God. you're his parents!

1031
00:57:14.752 --> 00:57:15.928
Oh...

1032
00:57:16.039 --> 00:57:18.593
Oh my god. look at me. I-I-I'm a mess.

1033
00:57:18.661 --> 00:57:21.860
W-Well. it's so great to finally meet you.

1034
00:57:22.841 --> 00:57:24.693
Please. come in. Come in.

1035
00:57:24.854 --> 00:57:25.886
Oh. hon...

1036
00:57:26.050 --> 00:57:26.853
Very friendly.

1037
00:57:27.219 --> 00:57:29.580
You must be exhausted.
Did you just get in?

1038
00:57:29.668 --> 00:57:31.466
Would you like something to drink?

1039
00:57:31.527 --> 00:57:33.637
Isabel. that is a great idea.

1040
00:57:33.698 --> 00:57:35.357
Why don't you get the drinks?
I love you.

1041
00:57:35.724 --> 00:57:37.990
-and I'll think of something.
-Okay.

1042
00:57:38.051 --> 00:57:39.546
Who wants a cold beer?

1043
00:57:39.618 --> 00:57:41.088
-Terrific.
-I'd love one.

1044
00:57:42.818 --> 00:57:44.964
Don't you dare tell them
anything until I come back.

1045
00:57:46.268 --> 00:57:47.745
She is wonderful.

1046
00:57:48.396 --> 00:57:50.730
Of course. there must be a lot
of good help around here.

1047
00:57:50.793 --> 00:57:53.114
I mean. just being so close to Mexico.

1048
00:57:53.598 --> 00:57:56.631
-My God. Alex. isn't this a company house?
-Such a warm people.

1049
00:57:56.939 --> 00:57:59.630
You would think that they could
afford a decent decorator.

1050
00:58:01.011 --> 00:58:01.930
Dad. Mom.

1051
00:58:02.520 --> 00:58:04.015
why don't you sit down?

1052
00:58:08.140 --> 00:58:08.965
What the hell is this?

1053
00:58:10.530 --> 00:58:11.022
Honey.

1054
00:58:11.448 --> 00:58:12.799
is there something wrong?

1055
00:58:17.584 --> 00:58:19.281
Yes. I have to tell...

1056
00:58:21.104 --> 00:58:23.138
Isabel where the bottle opener is.

1057
00:58:24.017 --> 00:58:25.497
So. how was Europe?

1058
00:58:26.081 --> 00:58:27.566
You came back soon.

1059
00:58:27.627 --> 00:58:28.428
Europe?

1060
00:58:29.142 --> 00:58:31.266
Alex said you were gone for the summer.

1061
00:58:31.445 --> 00:58:32.582
Oh. Alex.

1062
00:58:33.018 --> 00:58:34.301
you know better than that.

1063
00:58:34.362 --> 00:58:37.139
We hate Europe in the summer.
Too many tourists.

1064
00:58:37.200 --> 00:58:38.909
Europe in the summer?

1065
00:58:41.617 --> 00:58:42.673
You lied to me.

1066
00:58:44.250 --> 00:58:45.234
All this time.

1067
00:58:49.107 --> 00:58:51.671
No quiero que me digas una palabra.

1068
00:58:51.732 --> 00:58:52.729
Estoy harta de tus mentiras.

1069
00:58:52.790 --> 00:58:54.937
Es todo lo que me has dicho. mentiras.
Cobarde!

1070
00:58:56.255 --> 00:58:57.118
What does that mean?

1071
00:58:57.849 --> 00:59:00.143
That means you're a liar and a coward.
That's what it means.

1072
00:59:03.464 --> 00:59:05.426
It sounded so much prettier in Spanish.

1073
00:59:08.228 --> 00:59:09.600
Would you excuse me for a minute?

1074
00:59:12.158 --> 00:59:15.213
Sounds like somebody's about to get fired.

1075
00:59:19.445 --> 00:59:20.320
Isabel.

1076
00:59:20.891 --> 00:59:22.403
I was going to tell them.

1077
00:59:22.659 --> 00:59:23.248
When?

1078
00:59:23.498 --> 00:59:24.661
After the baby was born?

1079
00:59:24.722 --> 00:59:26.618
I didn't want to do it over the phone.

1080
00:59:27.438 --> 00:59:29.374
My father won't even speak to me.

1081
00:59:29.581 --> 00:59:32.119
But I went there. I told him the truth.

1082
00:59:32.756 --> 00:59:35.458
But you don't even have the
balls to pick up the phone...

1083
00:59:35.519 --> 00:59:37.273
and just let them know what's going on.

1084
00:59:44.745 --> 00:59:46.760
My family's not like yours. okay?

1085
00:59:46.821 --> 00:59:49.148
I never see them. I never talk to them.
I don't have dinners...

1086
00:59:49.209 --> 00:59:53.612
Excuses. excuses. excuses!
You should've told them.

1087
00:59:53.676 --> 00:59:55.086
I wanted to do it in person.

1088
00:59:55.147 --> 00:59:57.489
Okay? Why is that so hard
for you to understand?

1089
01:00:03.637 --> 01:00:05.335
Well. here's your big chance.

1090
01:00:11.800 --> 01:00:12.380
Mom.

1091
01:00:12.765 --> 01:00:13.324
Dad...

1092
01:00:14.532 --> 01:00:17.843
I have some interesting and exciting news.

1093
01:00:21.266 --> 01:00:23.576
I'd like you to meet Isabel Fuentes...

1094
01:00:25.191 --> 01:00:25.874
Whitman.

1095
01:00:27.308 --> 01:00:28.603
Oh. my God.

1096
01:00:38.879 --> 01:00:40.654
I let these people come. didn't I?

1097
01:00:40.823 --> 01:00:42.329
That doesn't mean I have to like it.

1098
01:00:42.807 --> 01:00:43.846
Mama. do something.

1099
01:00:44.053 --> 01:00:45.665
Why are you being so difficult?

1100
01:00:45.887 --> 01:00:48.052
Because as far as I'm concerned.

1101
01:00:48.113 --> 01:00:49.658
these people are not her in-laws

1102
01:00:49.719 --> 01:00:50.765
because she's not married.

1103
01:00:50.973 --> 01:00:53.126
And if she's not married.
she has no in-laws.

1104
01:00:53.610 --> 01:00:57.345
So. why am I celebrating the Cinco
de Mayo with complete strangers?

1105
01:00:57.406 --> 01:00:59.372
They're only strangers because
you won't talk to them.

1106
01:01:00.021 --> 01:01:00.988
Pues no Les voy a hablar.

1107
01:01:01.339 --> 01:01:02.007
Tomas.

1108
01:01:02.541 --> 01:01:04.444
either you act like the man I married.

1109
01:01:04.505 --> 01:01:06.575
or tonight. you sleep with the dogs.

1110
01:01:16.379 --> 01:01:19.049
I hope you have plenty of lotion on.

1111
01:01:20.346 --> 01:01:23.270
The desert sun kicks off
this water like a mirror.

1112
01:01:23.331 --> 01:01:24.042
Oh.

1113
01:01:24.670 --> 01:01:27.582
No. I think if we stay in the shade.

1114
01:01:27.947 --> 01:01:28.892
we'll be fine.

1115
01:01:29.447 --> 01:01:30.742
Suit yourselves.

1116
01:01:31.393 --> 01:01:32.679
Pity you didn't bring your suits.

1117
01:01:33.018 --> 01:01:35.838
Yes. oh. yes.
We didn't exactly plan for this.

1118
01:01:38.316 --> 01:01:40.417
Jesus Christ. is it hot?

1119
01:01:46.637 --> 01:01:48.066
Uh. senor.

1120
01:01:48.786 --> 01:01:50.123
I would like to tell you something.

1121
01:01:51.282 --> 01:01:53.738
I do not believe these kids have a clue...

1122
01:01:54.008 --> 01:01:55.835
what they are getting themselves into.

1123
01:01:56.319 --> 01:01:57.828
I couldn't agree with you more.

1124
01:01:58.320 --> 01:01:59.839
-Really?
-Absolutely.

1125
01:02:00.165 --> 01:02:02.161
Marriage is a serious commitment.

1126
01:02:02.222 --> 01:02:02.842
Well.

1127
01:02:03.065 --> 01:02:06.422
I happen to think that
it's terribly romantic.

1128
01:02:06.735 --> 01:02:08.055
Nan! Hon.

1129
01:02:08.603 --> 01:02:10.399
see. you're not helping.

1130
01:02:11.074 --> 01:02:12.656
I have to agree with her. Richard.

1131
01:02:12.997 --> 01:02:16.147
You men forget how foolish you
once were chasing after us.

1132
01:02:17.035 --> 01:02:18.149
This is different.

1133
01:02:18.781 --> 01:02:19.927
They are different.

1134
01:02:20.292 --> 01:02:23.404
They come from a different culture.
a different world.

1135
01:02:23.840 --> 01:02:26.117
It's hard enough to make a marriage work

1136
01:02:26.372 --> 01:02:27.919
without adding to it.

1137
01:02:28.362 --> 01:02:29.522
Listen to the man. Alex.

1138
01:02:30.054 --> 01:02:30.871
He has a point.

1139
01:02:31.926 --> 01:02:34.502
I think they're gonna start
spelling the big words soon.

1140
01:02:35.411 --> 01:02:37.306
Why can't you just be happy for us?

1141
01:02:37.480 --> 01:02:38.972
Because I'm afraid for you.

1142
01:02:39.738 --> 01:02:41.618
This whole thing never would have happened

1143
01:02:41.688 --> 01:02:42.880
if he hadn't gone after...

1144
01:02:42.941 --> 01:02:45.513
Now. now. now. wait just a second. Tomas.

1145
01:02:45.842 --> 01:02:47.272
It takes two to...

1146
01:02:47.921 --> 01:02:48.554
tango.

1147
01:02:48.820 --> 01:02:50.451
She is just as guilty as he is.

1148
01:02:50.518 --> 01:02:53.303
Now. let's just calm down. shall we?

1149
01:02:54.287 --> 01:02:55.583
They fell in love.

1150
01:02:55.954 --> 01:02:59.453
And love is a beautiful thing

1151
01:03:00.997 --> 01:03:02.881
Ask yourself this question. Isabelita:

1152
01:03:02.942 --> 01:03:04.084
Where will you live?

1153
01:03:04.417 --> 01:03:05.966
How will you raise your child?

1154
01:03:06.625 --> 01:03:07.677
We don't know yet.

1155
01:03:08.056 --> 01:03:08.755
You see?

1156
01:03:08.936 --> 01:03:10.871
Let's just start with the economics.

1157
01:03:11.476 --> 01:03:12.561
They will live in New York...

1158
01:03:13.198 --> 01:03:14.925
because that is where his job is.

1159
01:03:15.296 --> 01:03:17.796
And the religion will have to be Catholic.

1160
01:03:18.757 --> 01:03:19.589
Says who?

1161
01:03:20.129 --> 01:03:21.148
The mother is Catholic.

1162
01:03:22.007 --> 01:03:24.715
Whatever the mother is. the baby is.

1163
01:03:24.810 --> 01:03:27.413
And just what is the matter
with Presbyterian?

1164
01:03:28.022 --> 01:03:30.266
Presbyterian is not a religion.

1165
01:03:30.575 --> 01:03:31.873
I beg your pardon.

1166
01:03:32.119 --> 01:03:33.553
Thomas. Tomas. whatever...

1167
01:03:34.320 --> 01:03:35.866
This country was founded

1168
01:03:36.088 --> 01:03:38.939
by people who were escaping
religious persecution.

1169
01:03:39.034 --> 01:03:41.232
The Whitmans were one of them.

1170
01:03:41.293 --> 01:03:45.145
Sir. when the West was stolen from Mexico.

1171
01:03:45.248 --> 01:03:47.143
the Fuentes family made a vow...

1172
01:03:47.238 --> 01:03:49.158
that even though they took our land.

1173
01:03:49.219 --> 01:03:51.052
they'd never take our culture!

1174
01:03:51.113 --> 01:03:53.313
Culture? You call this 'culture'?

1175
01:03:53.806 --> 01:03:56.885
Guacamole and a ghetto blaster
in the middle of a desert?

1176
01:03:56.946 --> 01:03:57.408
Dad.

1177
01:03:57.469 --> 01:03:59.753
-Now you're offending Amalia's guacamole?
-Papa.

1178
01:03:59.814 --> 01:04:01.686
What's wrong with Amalia's guacamole?

1179
01:04:01.747 --> 01:04:03.273
In case you haven't noticed.

1180
01:04:03.648 --> 01:04:06.624
the white people are melting out here.

1181
01:04:15.202 --> 01:04:18.595
# Heat up 'til you sizzle #

1182
01:04:19.005 --> 01:04:21.619
# What a lovely way to burn #

1183
01:04:22.573 --> 01:04:25.196
# What a lovely way to burn

1184
01:04:26.121 --> 01:04:28.882
# What a lovely way to burn #

1185
01:04:32.384 --> 01:04:35.890
Isabel. it was 112 degrees.
I fried an egg on my head.

1186
01:04:36.159 --> 01:04:38.830
And he didn't mean 'white.'
He meant... He m...

1187
01:04:39.548 --> 01:04:41.257
He meant 'not tan.'

1188
01:04:42.113 --> 01:04:42.936
Don't go there.

1189
01:04:43.341 --> 01:04:46.388
Your father wasn't too helpful
with all that Catholic talk.

1190
01:04:47.347 --> 01:04:47.926
Alex.

1191
01:04:48.402 --> 01:04:50.838
the first time I realized I was pregnant.

1192
01:04:51.046 --> 01:04:55.172
I got stopped at a stop light
right in front of St. Viviana's.

1193
01:04:55.748 --> 01:04:56.684
You know what it was?

1194
01:04:57.651 --> 01:04:59.582
-It was a sign.
-Of what?

1195
01:05:00.766 --> 01:05:02.235
That the baby would be Catholic.

1196
01:05:02.583 --> 01:05:04.825
Then it's a good thing you weren't
stopped in front of an IHOP.

1197
01:05:05.905 --> 01:05:06.797
You think that's funny?

1198
01:05:06.867 --> 01:05:10.142
Look. Isabel. religion is
the opiate of the masses.

1199
01:05:10.483 --> 01:05:12.966
And country clubs are filled with racists.

1200
01:05:13.027 --> 01:05:14.291
Yes. Right. I agree.

1201
01:05:14.352 --> 01:05:16.516
But. do you really think
hanging a crucifix on a wall

1202
01:05:16.577 --> 01:05:18.178
is gonna protect you from anything?

1203
01:05:18.382 --> 01:05:19.399
As a matter of fact. I do.

1204
01:05:19.466 --> 01:05:21.802
I believe because I am a woman of faith.

1205
01:05:22.213 --> 01:05:24.023
The faith I have in that crucifix.

1206
01:05:24.084 --> 01:05:26.039
and the faith I have in us.

1207
01:05:26.476 --> 01:05:28.843
it all comes from the
same place inside of me.

1208
01:05:29.148 --> 01:05:29.757
Now.

1209
01:05:29.993 --> 01:05:31.156
you. on the other hand...

1210
01:05:32.755 --> 01:05:35.650
You're not even an active Presbyterian.

1211
01:05:36.012 --> 01:05:36.716
So.

1212
01:05:37.081 --> 01:05:39.487
why don't you want me to carry my faith

1213
01:05:39.548 --> 01:05:41.282
and my belief to our child?

1214
01:05:41.343 --> 01:05:43.444
It's a good way to be.
It's a good thing to do.

1215
01:05:43.505 --> 01:05:46.388
It's not the only way to be.
It's not the only thing to do.

1216
01:05:48.953 --> 01:05:49.993
Where are you going?

1217
01:05:50.230 --> 01:05:51.797
You're not my favourite person right now.

1218
01:05:51.859 --> 01:05:53.120
Yeah. well. you either.

1219
01:05:54.641 --> 01:05:55.744
Do you want my advice?

1220
01:05:56.604 --> 01:05:57.507
Get out now.

1221
01:05:58.097 --> 01:05:59.252
I'll even file it for you.

1222
01:05:59.706 --> 01:06:02.064
Ah. who said lawyers don't have hearts?

1223
01:06:02.142 --> 01:06:03.398
Hey! What did you expect?

1224
01:06:03.844 --> 01:06:05.944
You have a relationship built on heat.

1225
01:06:06.559 --> 01:06:07.688
It's like Vegas.

1226
01:06:07.809 --> 01:06:10.217
Why didn't they just build
this city on the fuckin' sun?

1227
01:06:10.358 --> 01:06:12.544
Maybe you're not the guy
to talk to about this.

1228
01:06:12.632 --> 01:06:15.623
No. I'm the perfect guy
'cause I know what you're trying to do.

1229
01:06:15.810 --> 01:06:17.097
You're tryin' to be the decent guy.

1230
01:06:17.158 --> 01:06:19.499
but I'm telling you. the longer you
put this off. the worse it'll be.

1231
01:06:19.560 --> 01:06:21.852
Put what off? I just said we had a fight.

1232
01:06:22.690 --> 01:06:24.367
You said a lot more than that. my friend.

1233
01:06:25.071 --> 01:06:26.090
Okay. Alex...

1234
01:06:26.476 --> 01:06:27.584
We're here to get a job done.

1235
01:06:27.645 --> 01:06:29.743
and in case you haven't noticed. we're
runnin' a little behind schedule.

1236
01:06:29.804 --> 01:06:32.072
Hey. can I help it if Cinco
de Mayo fell on a Tuesday?

1237
01:06:32.139 --> 01:06:34.842
Get your priorities straight before
the shit really hits the fan.

1238
01:06:35.981 --> 01:06:36.927
Why? What's up?

1239
01:06:37.427 --> 01:06:38.883
We had a little visit from OSHA.

1240
01:06:39.088 --> 01:06:40.448
Will you talk to the foreman?

1241
01:06:40.953 --> 01:06:43.031
We came this close to a red-tag shut down.

1242
01:06:46.024 --> 01:06:47.019
Oh. Jesus.

1243
01:06:47.767 --> 01:06:50.480
-All right. I will handle this. okay?
-Good.

1244
01:06:53.685 --> 01:06:55.248
Mrs. Gonzales. please.

1245
01:06:57.253 --> 01:06:58.833
Hi. Have a seat.

1246
01:07:02.369 --> 01:07:03.043
May I help you?

1247
01:07:03.104 --> 01:07:04.934
Isabel Fuentes. uh. Whitman.

1248
01:07:08.947 --> 01:07:09.855
Isabel.

1249
01:07:09.977 --> 01:07:10.811
Alex.

1250
01:07:11.221 --> 01:07:12.579
I thought you had to work.

1251
01:07:12.919 --> 01:07:16.011
I do. but I need to talk to you.

1252
01:07:16.283 --> 01:07:18.169
I need to talk to you too.

1253
01:07:18.590 --> 01:07:21.421
I feel really bad about the
way things have been going.

1254
01:07:22.059 --> 01:07:24.497
Oh. no. no. It was my fault.

1255
01:07:26.525 --> 01:07:28.775
Look. I haven't been
completely honest with you.

1256
01:07:31.732 --> 01:07:34.380
And I was thinking on the way over...

1257
01:07:35.583 --> 01:07:37.925
Hello. Isabel. How are we today?

1258
01:07:38.731 --> 01:07:39.628
We are fine.

1259
01:07:41.045 --> 01:07:43.147
Oh. you must be the father
I've heard so much about.

1260
01:07:43.516 --> 01:07:45.200
I'm Lisa Barnes. Alex Whitman.

1261
01:07:45.359 --> 01:07:46.930
You're just in time for the show.

1262
01:07:49.328 --> 01:07:50.268
You wanna watch?

1263
01:07:50.934 --> 01:07:51.792
Come over.

1264
01:07:56.323 --> 01:07:59.207
-Uh. is that gonna hurt her?
-Oh. no. it tickles.

1265
01:08:05.207 --> 01:08:06.734
Whoa. What is that?

1266
01:08:07.258 --> 01:08:08.528
That's your baby's heartbeat.

1267
01:08:09.946 --> 01:08:11.179
It's so fast.

1268
01:08:11.493 --> 01:08:12.402
It's normal.

1269
01:08:12.744 --> 01:08:13.687
Neat. huh?

1270
01:08:14.603 --> 01:08:15.354
Yeah.

1271
01:08:15.855 --> 01:08:16.618
Yeah.

1272
01:08:18.651 --> 01:08:19.661
There's the head.

1273
01:08:21.542 --> 01:08:22.639
There's a leg.

1274
01:08:25.295 --> 01:08:26.414
Wait a minute. Wait a minute.

1275
01:08:26.771 --> 01:08:27.277
Is...

1276
01:08:27.761 --> 01:08:28.853
Is that his...

1277
01:08:30.083 --> 01:08:31.892
Actually I think that's an arm.

1278
01:08:32.245 --> 01:08:34.576
It's a little too early
to determine the baby's sex.

1279
01:08:37.464 --> 01:08:38.171
Okay.

1280
01:08:38.509 --> 01:08:40.843
let's take the first picture of your baby.

1281
01:08:47.473 --> 01:08:48.352
I'm sorry.

1282
01:08:50.144 --> 01:08:50.889
Me too.

1283
01:08:52.786 --> 01:08:55.304
Jeff. I could hear his little heartbeat.

1284
01:08:55.372 --> 01:08:57.745
You know? I mean. it was going
ba-doom-boom. doom. ba-doom.

1285
01:08:57.806 --> 01:09:00.015
That's great.
I spoke to New York yesterday.

1286
01:09:00.076 --> 01:09:01.804
Guess who is three weeks
ahead of schedule?

1287
01:09:02.352 --> 01:09:05.138
-Charlie Peters doesn't have a life. okay?
-I'm just sayin'.

1288
01:09:05.370 --> 01:09:07.277
Hey. where the hell is my crane?

1289
01:09:07.736 --> 01:09:09.266
Foreman says first thing tomorrow.

1290
01:09:11.184 --> 01:09:12.444
Hello!

1291
01:09:12.698 --> 01:09:13.498
Hey-hey.

1292
01:09:13.559 --> 01:09:14.417
Hey. Isabel.

1293
01:09:14.605 --> 01:09:16.510
Wow. what are you doin' here?

1294
01:09:17.232 --> 01:09:18.688
I've come to kidnap you.

1295
01:09:19.836 --> 01:09:21.667
Alex. this is really not a good day.

1296
01:09:22.040 --> 01:09:24.064
Oh. don't make me hurt you. gringo.

1297
01:09:24.207 --> 01:09:27.214
It's his birthday.
and I won't take 'no' for an answer.

1298
01:09:28.149 --> 01:09:29.162
Will you cover for me?

1299
01:09:30.149 --> 01:09:31.033
Please?

1300
01:09:32.438 --> 01:09:33.480
Have a good time.

1301
01:09:34.145 --> 01:09:36.156
-Thank you. Jeff.
-Thank you. Jeff.

1302
01:09:36.377 --> 01:09:37.939
-Bye-bye.
-Bye.

1303
01:09:38.000 --> 01:09:38.878
Bye-bye

1304
01:09:39.484 --> 01:09:40.206
Bye.

1305
01:09:40.835 --> 01:09:41.827
So. where we goin'?

1306
01:09:42.859 --> 01:09:45.328
It's a surprise. Big surprise.

1307
01:09:49.821 --> 01:09:52.154
The very first time I came here.

1308
01:09:52.881 --> 01:09:55.890
my father told me this story
about a family of squirrels...

1309
01:09:55.956 --> 01:09:58.462
-that lived on the plateau.
-Mm-hmm.

1310
01:09:58.550 --> 01:10:01.400
He said that one day the canyon split.

1311
01:10:02.150 --> 01:10:04.742
Half of the squirrels
ended up on the North Rim...

1312
01:10:04.829 --> 01:10:06.650
and the other half on the South Rim.

1313
01:10:07.484 --> 01:10:09.801
Over time. the two families
became different.

1314
01:10:10.562 --> 01:10:12.326
each one adjusting
to their own environment.

1315
01:10:13.000 --> 01:10:15.455
The ones to the north are dark.

1316
01:10:16.391 --> 01:10:18.899
bushy-tailed and have bigger ears.

1317
01:10:19.538 --> 01:10:22.010
The ones to the south are leaner.

1318
01:10:22.272 --> 01:10:24.761
meaner and much prettier.

1319
01:10:26.523 --> 01:10:28.081
And even though they look different

1320
01:10:28.734 --> 01:10:30.335
and they act different.

1321
01:10:31.123 --> 01:10:33.467
they are the exact same squirrel.

1322
01:10:34.866 --> 01:10:37.061
They just grew up on different sides.

1323
01:10:40.705 --> 01:10:42.768
And this canyon between them?

1324
01:10:46.619 --> 01:10:47.995
Will they ever be able to cross it?

1325
01:10:50.442 --> 01:10:51.688
Well...

1326
01:10:53.352 --> 01:10:55.594
I've been thinking
about making you a deal.

1327
01:10:57.286 --> 01:10:59.623
If we can stay here until the baby's born.

1328
01:11:01.265 --> 01:11:02.209
I'll move to New York.

1329
01:11:03.270 --> 01:11:06.151
Isabel. that's so great.
Well. I'm not saying I'll like it.

1330
01:11:06.877 --> 01:11:08.081
But I'll give it a try.

1331
01:11:08.872 --> 01:11:09.724
You got a deal.

1332
01:11:11.591 --> 01:11:13.535
Good. Then I can give you your present.

1333
01:11:15.413 --> 01:11:17.909
-You mean there's more.
-Uh-huh.

1334
01:11:19.537 --> 01:11:21.827
I called my new mother-in-law.

1335
01:11:22.466 --> 01:11:24.692
and I asked her to do me a little favour.

1336
01:11:25.085 --> 01:11:25.887
Okay.

1337
01:11:26.910 --> 01:11:28.067
This arrived today.

1338
01:11:43.764 --> 01:11:45.352
I can't believe you did this.

1339
01:11:46.664 --> 01:11:49.234
Who said you can't have the
best of both worlds. hmm?

1340
01:11:54.399 --> 01:11:56.694
This is the most wonderful
birthday I've ever had.

1341
01:12:03.750 --> 01:12:05.714
Okay. you think this is good?

1342
